# UgaTaima Desert Map
#
# Symbols resolve via assets/tiles.yaml for the "desert" biome (see the
# data-driven legend in the map viewer for the authoritative list).
# Tiles used here:
# . = sand (walkable)   T = Sand Dune   A = Large Dune (blocking)
# R = Moss-covered Stone (corners)   W = oasis water (blocking)
# P = Desert Palm (blocking, environment sprite)
# Spawns / markers:
# n = bandit   @ = NPC / special-tile placeholder
# Dragons (4 corners, one per element — all named "Dragon"):
#   d = fire (base)   r = dark (dragon_red)   e = poison (dragon_green)
#   y = air/storm (dragon_gold)
#
# Layout: a central oasis (desert merchant + red teleporter) plus two small
# palm oases, each guarded by 5 bandits (clearing an oasis's bandits drops a
# 500-gold chest at its water — see desert.clear_encounters in map_configs.yaml).
# The 4 corner dragons are the MAIN-QUEST target: the "dragon_slayer" quest
# (assets/quests.yaml) counts kills by monster NAME, and all four share
# name "Dragon", so any 4 colors complete it. Keep exactly 4 dragons unless
# you also change the win condition / target_count.
